        "class": "ital",
        "text": "wherein.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Many of the better MSS. give the relative pronoun in the feminine, as agreeing with “offerings,” and indicating that he was, as it were, occupied with them at the very time when the Jews from Asia found him, not profaning the Temple, but purified with all the completeness which the Nazarite vow required.",
