  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Whereupon,.... Or \"among which\"; while the apostle was busy about the offerings of the Nazarites: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "certain Jews from Asia found me purified in the temple; and therefore could not be said to profane it; this he observes in answer to the charge of his attempting to profane it, and acquaints the governor how that was; as that having joined himself to four men that had a vow upon them, and being in the temple purifying himself with them, certain Jews that came from Ephesus, in Asia, who knew him there, and had a pique against him, found him here; not profaning the temple, as they pretended, but acting according to the worship and service of it; and that, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "neither with a multitude; for there were but four men with him; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "nor with tumult; making any noise and riot, or stirring up persons to sedition and rebellion. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "nor with tumult; making any noise and riot, or stirring up persons to sedition and rebellion. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
